snippet.textDisplay: Yet another fusion of two folk songs done beautifully by Coke Studio! Fizza and Mulazim complement each other very well. Fizza has a beautiful throw in her voice displaying command at places while being technically sound with her harkats. On the other hand Mulazim brings out the romantic element so beautifully! He is soft and reflects the emotions of a lady so well! Amazing composition overall! :)

snippet.textDisplay: Coke studio has blended two conflicting emotional states with such mastery; amazing.!! On one hand the bride is in despair at the thought of leaving her parent's home and is asking the bridegroom to take his time in coming over with his wedding party. On the other hand though, she's in love with her man and is full of hope for her new life. What a rich and wonderful culture we have in the sub-continent.
